[0m[32m[TOOL][0m [32m+Subject: [PATCH] rar4 reader: protect copy_from_lzss_window_to_unp from too-big or too-small length
[0m[32m[TOOL][0m [32m+
[0m[32m[TOOL][0m [32m+copy_from_lzss_window_to_unp unnecessarily took an `int` parameter where both of its callers were holding a `size_t`. A lzss opcode chain could be cosntructed that resulted in a negative copy length, which when passed into memcpy would result in a very, very large positive number. Switching copy_from_lzss_window_to_unp to take a `size_t` allows it to properly bounds-check length. In addition, this patch also ensures that `length` is not itself larger than the destination buffer.
